  "prompt": "Do middle class people shop at thrift stores?",
  "response": "Yes, middle class people often shop at thrift stores for a variety of reasons. These can include finding unique items, saving money, supporting sustainable fashion, or enjoying the thrill of treasure hunting for special deals. Thrift stores can offer a wide range of products, from clothing and accessories to home goods and furniture, appealing to a broad demographic that includes middle class shoppers. Moreover, the growing trend of conscious consumerism and sustainable living has made thrift shopping popular among people from various income brackets who are mindful of their consumption choices.",
